description:
Suraya Mohamed | December 29, 2025
In October, the third international edition of the Tiny Desk concert series launched at the Google office in São Paulo, Brazil. Recorded live in front of an audience, the performances are selected and produced by Anonymous Content Brazil and Amabis with input from NPR Music. You can watch all of the shows on Tiny Desk Brasil’s YouTube channel. Here is the series premiere featuring João Gomes. The description below, translated here from Portuguese to English, was written by journalist and contributor Lorena Calábria.

On his way to Tiny Desk Brasil, João Gomes was approached by a fan outside his hotel. When asked, “What are you doing in São Paulo?” the singer promptly replied, “I'm going there to make history!” It is with this conviction that the artist from Pernambuco inaugurates the Brazilian version, representing contemporary Northeastern Brazilian music.
